  <datafield tag="545" ind1="1" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">D. C. Allen was a Three Oaks, Michigan, book dealer and collector of material on the House of David, an adventist cult founded in England. The leader of this cult was Benjamin Purnell who made Benton Harbor, Michigan, his home and the site of his followers' business activities.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Photographs (prints, film negatives, and glass negatives) and postcards depicting House of David leaders, business enterprises, facilities, and group activities and community outreach; include photographs of community founders, Benjamin and Mary Purnell, of House of David baseball team, and of such visitors as boxer Joe Louis.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
